details.description:
Freshly Baked, Everyday

Since our launch into the United States in 2004, TOUS les JOURS [meaning "everyday" in French] has developed into a reputable neighborhood bakery specializing in French-Asian inspired baked goods, hand crafted beverages and bold, flavorful coffee and espresso made with the finest ingredients.

With a commitment to using only the finest ingredients, our products are known for their unique flavors and wholesome qualities. Our skilled bakers create a wide array of delicious treats that are freshly baked and ready to be enjoyed by our customers seeking exceptional taste and quality.

reviews_data.review_text: Stopped in here because Snooze was taking too long to seat us,  and O...EM..GEE!!! If you like, no, IF YOU LOVE PASTRIES AND BREADS, you gotta hit this place up! The selection is  very decent for light pastries (croissants, breads, Danish, etc), not to mwntuonthe various flavors of croissants and refrigerated desserts! And the crew is amazing! Stepping in here felt like stepping into a bistro in Europe!

review_questions.Parking options: Free parking lot, Free street parking

reviews_data.review_text: My french friend love it. She said it taste so authentic and she felt like back in her home country!
The cafe vibe is cozy and inviting, perfect for a casual coffee break or a sweet treat on the go.

All our food (custard bun, red bean bun, melon bread, croissant, and macaroons) tastes like febreeze air freshener. I literally have nothing else bad to say. Surely it could have been a one off occurrence, I’ve only been here once. For every single item I listed to have that chemical air freshener taste though…yeah I would never go here again.
among the worst locations

Love this place! Staff is friendly and helpful! Love their cakes and pastries, even the savory ones like curry and kimchi! The sandwich with the cheese on the outside and ham on the inside is so good. Try their honey lavender matcha. My faaaav!
Best cakes in Charlotte can't go wrong go in there
Very good service from the staff and the great taste from the food. Clean area,  grea atmosphere.  I will come back  and bring my family and friends.  Continue this way.

Love this location! It’s a bit smaller than the others but feels more cozy. The staff is always super friendly and help me with coffee recommendations when I don’t know what to order. Never had an issue with ordering and their cakes are always a big hit at family parties.
Love Tous!!! The staff is so friendly and welcoming!!!

I’ve been coming to this bakery for years, and I have to say — the recent changes in management have truly elevated the experience! The atmosphere feels warm and welcoming, and the staff are friendly and attentive. You can really tell they care about providing great service and high-quality products.

The pastries and bread are as delicious as ever (if not better!), and everything tastes so fresh. The new management has introduced some exciting new items while keeping the classic favorites we all love.

It’s clear they are focused on creating a positive environment for both customers and the team. Change can be tough, but in this case, it feels like a step in the right direction.

Highly recommend stopping by if you haven't visited in a while — you’ll definitely notice the difference!

Customer service was terrible. I felt very disrespected despite doing nothing wrong. I felt as if the person working at the cash register had some sort of ingrained hate specifically towards me based on their tone and body language. They didn’t do this to other people who were in the line. I don’t understand why I had to be the unlucky target. Totally ruined my day. 🙁💔👎🏾
Great customer service, and the pastry was amazing!! Love this for first time experience

Adorable bakery. Has a seating area. Staff greets you immediately & they were super friendly. Great customer service & great pastries. They are pretty creative with drinks that have matcha. Definitely coming here more often.

Incredible place! Everything is fantastic! And the service is outstanding!
Claudia Ribas
Amazing pastries and cute little spot.
One of my favorite coffee shops in charlotte!!! The workers here are friendly and the pastries are amazing!

I’m a regular at this place. I’m obsessed with their honey lavender matcha that I get it at least once a week. The donuts are also very delicious.  I am always greeted every time I walk through the door. Everyone is always so sweet. Sometimes I sit at the back of the other place and the staff are always telling me to go sit down and they will bring my drink out to me when they don’t have to. They’re part of the reason I keep coming back.
The atmosphere was amazingly beautiful the food was great and the service was great

Me, my daughter and grandson were so excited to try this place Tous Les Jours Southend on Sunday, June 1, 2025. We went to the South Blvd location. As we entered, we were never greeted with a "hello" or anything. We looked at most of the pastries and desserts that were in the cases, but still no greeting or acknowledgement by the staff that we were even there. We finally asked one of the employees if they usually greet customers as they come in, and the young man replied, "yes" sarcastically. So we ended up leaving. One thing about me, if I'm not greeted or acknowledged after entering an establishment, I will not spend one penny there. We were so disappointed by the way we were ignored. We will not be back either! I wouldn't give them not even one star.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hey Tammy, 

We do apologize about the situation, but upon talking to our employees there seem to be a misunderstanding.  One of our employee did greet your party while he was washing the dishes, and our other employee at the time was helping another customer.  Again we do apologize for the misunderstanding, but the greeting might just be covered by the water.

reviews_data.review_text: They need better staff, the staff there is condescending and got my order wrong. I ordered an ice latte and they gave me a Frappuccino I’m very disappointed and the other time they thought I wasn’t there and spoke bad about me as the customer this is just very disappointing and unprofessional
The best tasting n fresh cakes and macaroons for sure. Used to be a fan for this place in other states and no exceptions here. But the price has definitely gone higher in 5 years.

작지만  깔끔하고 잘 정렬되어있었음.
바게뜨가 한국 뚜레쥬르 바게뜨랑 다르게 생겼음.
소금빵 맛있기를  기대하고있음. 집에 가서 먹어야지  ㅎㅎ
Nice selection of French desserts. Their cloud cake is a unique recipe.
i love this place. always here
Walked in at 7:40 PM and was told they stop serving lattes after 7:30 PM. Seriously? It’s a café, not a bank. If you close at 8, why cut off drinks early? Pretty disappointing.
A French bakery conveniently located in Southend, however the melon bread and blueberry cake lacked richness in their taste. Spend your money elsewhere.
Absolutely stunning bakery. Service is acceptable.

Demasiado rico todo!! Muy buena combinación de repostería francesa y asiática, las bebidas también estuvieron muy buenas, el personal atento, aunque pocas personas y en un momento se llenó y hubo un poco de demora.
Staff is RUDE - food is great tho

Decided to drop by while in Charlotte because not many of TLJ in the area. Options are limited compared to their bigger locations but I found what i was looking for. The pastries, cakes and drinks were good. Taking off one star for the female cashier who was rude and had a sarcastic attitude. The guy who made our drinks was nice though.

Because of the limited space, I’ll give the atmosphere a 4. It’s fine to sit but if all few seats are taken, you’ll need to find another place to relax. The food is light and to perfection. There is a desert for everyone here. The cakes are not dense and I would be careful for those who like dense cakes.

The hours are accessible for everyone and just like every bakery, unfortunately the early birds get the best food.

I haven’t tried their drinks or was inclined to go to their boba shop to order anything.

The baristas always have a positive attitude even with a large amount of people.

Personally I like the simple classics like their croissants and vanilla or cookies and cream macaroons. I have eaten their cloud cakes, other macaroons, soft breads (milk cream is my fav as it’s basic).

It’s a fun place to try different things and share amongst friends and when you find your favorite- go back for more.

So we walked in yesterday afternoon, and I asked for iced coffee, black. The young lady that was attending the counter literally replied: “no, we don’t have that”. I look up at the menu and clearly see iced coffee listed as an option. I then said: “ok… can I have an americano, iced?” as I read off the menu and she then proceeded to make the said iced coffee. Why was she so quick to say no to my request, just because I didn’t ask for what was on the menu? No Customer Service or people skills! Coffee was just ok and mango doughnut had too much crème.

I specifically drove 1.5 hours to try their croissants as it's something my kid and I love to do. Find cute bakery's with our favorites pastry's. When you enter the building the atmosphere is less than enthusiastic. I felt like I was coming in during a closing shift at 2pm. The doughnuts were dry but it was midday when I got it. Cream filled doughnut was great, croissants were buttery and flakey as well as the raspberry danish. Cute place, but the outward appearance  is begging you to spend time in there but the employees give off a get in and get out attitude. Wasn't really pleasant but the bake goods were pretty good overall.

This place is a solid spot for fresh pastries and coffee. Their almond and strawberry croissants are flaky and rich. The mango and strawberry croissants are super light and not too sweet. Everything is freshly made and baked. The staff is friendly, and the place is cozy with a great ambiance. Definitely worth checking out if you’re in the area.

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Strawberry Croissant, Mango Croissant, Almond Croissant, Blueberry Muffin

reviews_data.review_text: My favourite backery place. I first tried it in Korea and I am really happy I can enjoy it here too. People is lovely and the food is wonderful as always
Immaculate vibes and super good pastries honestly.  So happy I discovered this place!

This is one of my go to places for a last minute cake.

I am appreciative of the little kit that is given with the purchase of a whole cake (serving utensil, match, & candles)

There is a little bit of everything for everyone.
There are also some savory options if you're not craving something sweet.

Depending on the time of day, getting in/ out of this location may be an issue (I think it just depends on traffic) , other than that, no other concerns.

This was our first time going to this bakery. It was really pretty and the atmosphere was nice and comfortable. It's mostly self serve which takes a lot if pressure off when trying a new place where there's a lot of options. However, the only negative thing was the lady checking us out. She was very rude and didn't have good customer service skills. Didn't even greet us in and spoke to us very aggressively and bluntly when we were checking out. I normally don't make a review like this but since it was our first time there it just felt necessary. Will try a different location next time.
Croissants and Tiramisu are my favorite breakfast options . Love the combo!!!
Muy bien el servicio es excelente y el producto es delicioso lo recomiendo

I searched out this location via Google and was excited about the the purchase of the Chocolate heart cake for my wife on Valentine Day, presentation was beautiful, but the cake was awful and lacked the taste of anything resembling Chocolate, for the price point we were very disappointed, if you're a true chocolate lover proceed with caution!!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hey Billy, we do apologize for the situation, can you please email us at tljsouthend@gmail.com.

reviews_data.review_text: I absolutely love the matcha at Tous les Jours! If you’re a matcha fan, you have to try the matcha cream and strawberry croissant—it’s the perfect combo. The flaky croissant with the creamy matcha and fresh strawberries is heavenly. Highly recommend stopping by for this treat!

Bad service, stale cakes( as well as the cream in one of their banana bread was wrong - it was not whipped cream), uncomfortable chairs (seemed like this cafe is more focused towards female customers)
Everything I had was delicious. I totally get all the hype that I have heard from different people. The workers were all very friendly and very accommodating. I will definitely be coming back.

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Corn Cheese Donuts, Assorted Pastries, Almond Croissant

reviews_data.review_text: Super cute little cafe, well worth the drive!
Really enjoyable dessert place to grab a quick bite or sit and enjoy. Their stuffed strawberry croissants were absolutely chef kiss!!!

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Strawberry Croissant, Apple Turnover, Cloud Cake 3

reviews_data.review_text: Dry pastries
Good cakes
Earl gray macaron was great
So happy I discovered this bakery. The pastries are out of this world and the staff is so nice, so friendly.
Nice place for Bekery but small parking lot.
Pre-ordered a Cloud Cake for my mom’s birthday and it came out beautifully. Staff 10/10! Would recommend!!!

Stopped in to satisfy a sweet craving and Tous Les didn't disappoint. The workers were pleasant and the store was very clean. We purchased several types of pastries to get a feel of the quality. Everything was very fresh and delicious. There is very limited seating on the stores front area but more in the back.
Parking is very hard .

Do not buy cakes from this place. I ordered my daughter’s birthday cake from here and the Assistant manager explained the sizes and prices and I orders an 8 inch cake a simple vanilla cloud cake. And I paid $59 and when I realized that they gave me a 6 inch the smallest cake they got. Also when you called to let them know that I’m sending my daughter to pick up the cake they were trying to sell me the happy birthday sign. Which was $4 when the assistant manager already explained that the cake came with a happy birthday sign in chocolate so the Assistant manager or the store manager Tiffany couldn’t be trusted. They should be ashamed for charging so much money for a 6 inch cake. I work in the food industry as a GM and if I was the Manager there If this happened I would resign immediately. This company has three locations and I bet this maybe how they opened two new stores by cheating customers. I would never step into this store and will make sure to let everyone I know about this place-
Also I purchased small mocha called that’s packaged it tasted stale and upon checking the best by date was expired already. Customers it’s better to buy freshly made cakes at publics for less where they constantly check on the expiration dates.
Makes you wonder if the NC health department needs visit these bakeries more frequently.

I love the other location but for some reason this location is hard to keep giving chances. It’s closer to me and no matter how early you go items are never out/stocked properly. A lot of items are packed up now which makes the items very wet and soggy. For some items it would be impossible to put inside a toaster to hit due to its contents for example the mango doughnut. It’s very disappointing trying to give this location a try and being disappointed each time. I will have to be willing to make the drive out for better quality.

I’ve ordered my daughter birthday cakes from here a few times. She absolutely loves Tous Les Jours cakes. Their cakes are always so delicious, they never disappoint. This facility is small and cozy and not much parking. Staff were extremely friendly. I would definitely recommend.
Cute place.

Loved everything about this bakery. The breads and cake were so delicious! I bought so much to try! I even bought two drinks to try. The good thing is the bakery even gave free complimentary water if you didn’t want to purchase a drink. The atmosphere was very calming. Mind you, I did go to the bakery on a weekday around 4:30ish when it wasn’t so busy. I’m sure it’s busy on the weekends.
Ricos y frescos dulces son perfectos. Y hay variedad en sabores.
Just found my new fav dessert spot! I will be back
My favorite bakery in Charlotte , many items but my favorite is their chocolate covered croissants and strawberry cloud cake .
Amazing bakery items!
Such a cute spot! The food is to die for and the staff is really friendly! Prices are also amazing. Only downside is the parking isn’t great😅 thankfully there’s a garage across the street!

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Strawberry Croissant, Assorted Pastries, Almond Croissant

reviews_data.review_text: It's always nice to go to Tous Les Jours, nice French-Korean Bakery, good combination. Service is the best.

Delicious fresh baked goods with a cozy atmosphere and welcoming staff.

We tried multiple sweet and savory treats and everything was fresh and yummy.

I wish they had a larger dinning area with more tables as it got crowded really quickly.

Great experience overall. Highly recommend this place.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much!! We have more seating in the back!

reviews_data.review_text: My new favorite go to spots to wfh! Pastries are delicious! Atmosphere was very cute! The person that helped me a lot was Simon he answered all my questions and was really friendly! Definitely will be coming back regularly!

Beautiful Cafe & Great staff! Southend location of Tour Le Jour is smaller, but the ambiance & service is top-notch! Everybody must try, it’s such a great place to work, socialize. Music is always amazing.

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Strawberry Croissant, Assorted Pastries, Blueberry Muffin

reviews_data.review_text: I’m visiting from Savannah Georgia and this place was amazing tasted delicious it was so cute and the two girls in the front were so sweet definitely will come back when we visit again.

Popped in to see if the prices were any better than back East. Sure enough, it was about $2-3 cheaper, so I couldn't resist grabbing one even though we had dinner plans. The staff was super friendly, and that bread was so good, we came back after dinner and picked up two more.

That milk cream bread is no joke - it might just be the best thing Tous les Jours has going. Seriously, it's a winner no matter where you get it!
Great choice of pastries, cakes and drinks. There are couple tables to sit down and couple parking spots. Very tiny space with cozy atmosphere.

I used to love coming here for fresh pastries but now they are wrapping each individual pastry in plastic and they are now soggy and sad instead of crisp and fresh. Why did you all do this? It defies logic to put fresh pastries into plastic…
reviews_data.owner_answer: First of all we would like to thank you for being a loyal customer.  Due to rising temperatures and humidity the flies and gnats are becoming a big problem in our bakery, and wrapping them is the best solution for everyone to still be able to enjoy our bake goods.  We suggest to the pastry in the toaster oven or air fryer for a couple minutes, that way it will be crispy again.  Thank you again for visiting, we do apologize for this inconvenience.

reviews_data.review_text: Strawberry cloud cake and  mango could piece was good
Place is small but the food tastes good. Their cloud cake and kimchi croquette is one of my fav.

Starting to notice all of the Tous Le Jours locations are either cutting back or just removing all of the savory items off their selection of baked goods entirely. This was the only spot left in the surrounding Charlotte area that still carried the hotdog breads, and sadly, they are no longer here. Very disappointing. One of the only reasons I even visit. Not much of a sweets person, so depriving a clientele base that prefer "savory" over "sweets" seems ill-advised. 😒😮‍💨
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hey Louis, sorry for the inconvenience. We will be bring the savory items back soon we just removed for now, we are doing some adjustments.

reviews_data.review_text: I loved this place but recently they have not been making any of the savory foods, of course their sweet treats are great but the main reason I keep coming back is for their savory breakfast/brunch items. Now that they are not serving them I will unfortunately have to find another bakery to visit - until they bring back the croquettes.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Jodi, sorry for the inconvenience we will definitely be bring back all the savory food. We are in the process of getting our croquet warmer fixed.

reviews_data.review_text: The breads and desserts were delicious! Customer service was good, and the atmosphere was pleasant. There are many delicious options to choose from.

I tried this charming French-Asian bakery and was blown away by the innovative fusion of flavors and textures. The pastries, such as the croissants, donuts with passion fruit-manggo filling and varieties of cakes with matcha and fruity flavors, were familiar, exotic  and a delightful twist to traditional French baked goods. The bakery's commitment to using high-quality, locally sourced ingredients shone through in every bite, making it a must-visit destination for anyone looking to indulge in a unique and delicious culinary experience. As a Filipino, the glutinous rice donut reminded me of home and the dessert that my grandma loves to whip when  I was young. Indeed , mus-visit  !!

Walked in at open and had a nasty encounter with employee!!! 1st. ... only 10% of their baked goods were even out with multiple people working??? A young female was super nasty, corrected me with so much attitude and horrible conduct even after I apologized and left a tip (for the other sweet girl). At the end of checking out, I nicely mention to her that there are a few gnats in the bakery case - she never looked up at me and had an irritated face the entire time. I get it ... its morning time and you gotta work but learn to treat and talk to people with love. The other girl in there is always a doll, FYI.
Good pastry options. Great service.

Went here on a whim just looked up close bakeries , and I there were so many good options I  like barely decided I ended up leaving with 5 items came out to 27 dollars and everything was so good !! Literally blown away definitely coming back to try more and get coffee next time!

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Mango Cream Donut, Apple Turnover, Almond Croissant

reviews_data.review_text: Stopped here for the first time after leaving Snooze in the same strip. I'm so happy we did. Lots of fresh bakery items as well as lattes, tea, coffee, and Frappuccinos. We purchased the Caramel Apple Pie danish to take home. There is limited seating. Outdoor parking. Pleasant personnel.  We will be returning.

Absolutely live this place!
-it’s all fresh and made daily
- The cake is SO GOOD! It’s fluffy and is topped with a whipped frosting
- Whatever they don’t sell they typically donate it to local business
- In my opinion cheap prices

Tous les Jours which means “every day” in French is a South Korean bakery franchise. This place is one of the finest bakeries with fantastic ambience. Coming to pastry section, We have ordered Guava Danish, Strawberry Croissant and Chocolate croissant. Guava Danish was the winner. Green tea cloud cake and choco cloud cake were light, mouth watering and goes very well with latte. Raisin bread was fluffy, aromatic and has the right amount I of sweetness. Caramel cheesecake was little bit over sweet. Coming to coffee, Iced tiramisu latte, vanilla latte, lavender latte and cappuccino were outstanding.
Staff are not friendly. The place was dirty and seemed junky. We actually love this franchise and was disappointed by this location. I’d recommend to go to South Park and not waste your time.
Shaniyah and Mozi were amazing explaining the menu and making suggestions. Wonderful customer service we will be back, great experience for our 1st time
The selection is amazing, the treats are all tasty. A good mix of savory and sweet. All the drinks are great, the place is cute. I would come here everyday if I could.
Literally the best cakes in Charlotte, so delicious, the inside of the store is always clean and the staff are amazing! Super accommodating and always make sure I leave happy.
Delicious!

im french and this is my favorite bakery in charlotte so far

chocolate avalanche: 12/10
strawberry bread: 22/10
croque-monsieur: 10/10

and the strawberry lemonade with a touch of carbonation 😩😩😩😩 made my day

excited to try a lot more things next time we visit

parking sucks tho but the pastries are worth it
I was so excited to visit this place as soon as moved here. Absolutely stunning bakery, delicious foods. will more than likely be back.

Update: went here again on a Sunday and some of the pastries honestly tasted a bit old and stale, not daily fresh but from yesterday. Bit disappointing.

Tried this cafe for the first time and it was great! The pastries were fresh and absolutely delicious! Staff was nice and everything was very clean and pristine. Highly recommend!

The place is really small. There weren't a lot of people inside but it was still a little hard to get around. I like to take my time looking at things, even more so since this was my first time here, but each time I would stop and look it felt like I was holding the people behind me up. Despite this, they offer a TON of baked goods. The staff were incredibly friendly as well. I got a honey castella, honeydew melon bread, taro loaf, honey mochi pancakes, and an iced red velvet latte. They were okay, a little stale but this may have been due to the fact that I ate them at home and not in the store. The red velvet latte was okay too, it didn't really taste like red velvet until I reached the pieces at the bottom of the cup. Overall, not bad but I just wish it was bigger and the seating wasn't so cramped. If I come here again, it will be for the honeydew melon bread 😋
Absolutely wonderful!!!
Fresh baked pastries, bread, and desserts that are OMG amazing!!! They have the best service and even the customers can sell you on what’s good. A hidden treasure in the Queen City.

Heamy fellow Charlatans or soon to be visitors. When in the Queen City, Southend  is where you wanna be if you love French pastries. Tous less Jours is a very warm, posh, and great spot to have great coffee & pastries all day. Just make sure when you go their you experience Brittany's great customer service and lovely smile, Mike's welcoming presence and of course Mozi's craving coffee creations. She's great on detail and meticulous on how she crafts your drink. Also Worker is normally somewhere helping the entire show run smoothly. Thanks guys for the great experience, I shall continue to be a patronizing customer 👌🏿

Finally, I made my way to visit this location for the Yelp experience. First off, this is located right off South Blvd, and let me say parking is rough! There are only a few spaces in front of the shop, and you also have to deal with that rough south end traffic. I went during my lunch break, which I took early just to beat lunchtime traffic. There was no traffic and about 2 parking spaces to choose from. The shop itself is super cute and small. Upon entering, you are greeted with a variety of pastry and bread selections. The ladies at the counter were super nice and helpful. You get a tray in the beginning and your pair of tongs and start selecting any pieces you would like. I got the spinach and feta Danish, which I read tastes better warming up in the oven, which I'm so excited. I ended up wanting to purchase chocolate filled fluffy donut, which I'm so excited to try out! I also bought a vanilla latte, which was def. Needed for this cold weather. It was not too expensive as I thought it would be, and they were actually reasonably prices $3+. I did find out they have other locations, which I def do. Intend on visiting.

Everything here was so good. I love trying new bakeries and this one did not disappoint. For a first-timer, the setup was a little confusing,  it I did like the self-serve aspect since they do get pretty  busy.

Easy to find with one of the most awkward parking lots I’ve seen, Tous Les Jours is an amazing bakery. You walk in the door and the smells immediately make your stomach growl in anticipation.

The two young ladies working there were lovely and polite. They became quite busy soon after I arrived but remained calm, cool and collected.

I had a caramel frappe and a spinach feta pastry while there. Both were very yummy. One of the young ladies packed my to-go bag professionally so nothing was squished by the time I got home.

Everything was so fresh, delicious, and affordable. Can’t wait to go back.

Phenomenal!!! We travel all over for my husbands job. I believe I came across this place from a blog on Pinterest and had it saved on Google maps as a place I wanted to go. We were in town and went here last minute. I don’t have a single sweet tooth but my husband and son do. I can’t even tell you what all they got but I got a piece of strawberry cake, a pumpkin something or other and one thing that looked like a sugar doughnut but was filled with cheese. We bought about $50 of random things because we don’t normally stop by places like this. Even after a few days in the fridge everything was SO good. Nothing was too sweet and the staff was beyond helpful and nice. I’d love to stop by again if we have time before we leave town. If your thinking about trying this place, just do it! I can’t say enough good things about it! Good job y’all!!
Excellent service, the desserts are delicious as is the coffee. I am a coffee lover
Everything looked and tasted amazing! Had a hard time choosing. Everything was so fresh. The staff was so friendly! Vanilla latte was delicious!
Everything I’ve tried here has been excellent and tastes extremely fresh (macarons, croquettes, croissants) and staff has been polite every time I’ve come in! Can’t wait to try more.

I heard their name from my friends in Boston so tried the one in Charlotte. Coffee and cakes were excellent. I wish the place was bigger. It is not a place for having your coffee and working from there.
Amazing deserts, park at chipotle in the morning

This was our second time visiting this bakery and first visit to this particular location. The selection was great, everything looked fresh & delicious, staff was friendly and informative, and we enjoyed everything we purchased. Mango cream donut is one of my favs!

This one is my favorite... always the freshest. All their employees seem so nice, the fact they put certain foods in a heater where the other locations doesn't and it's always full of product ... needless to say I'm in one or the other multiple times a week... they take a whole lot of my money but worth it

Cute cozy spot for coffee and exceptional pastries. Limited seating. All of the sweet pastries deserve a try. I ate as much as I could for the two days I was in town. Quality coffee and attentive staff.
The best food & service,good place
Great atmosphere.  Wonderful customer service.  Amazing pastries.
I like how you can pick your own items.  Very good!

I didn't appreciate the service I received from the manager. She was helping out at the cash register. She stopped being friendly when I looked for a coupon I saw on ig.

The pastries are good! They don't quite compare to how they taste in Korea, but they take care of the itch that I have for French-Korean baked goods

Las muchachas fueron muy amables con nosotros , supimos de este lugar y decidimos ir porque no se encuentra lugares así aquí con panes y dulces que se vean y sepan deliciosos. Lo recomiendo no son costosos tampoco tan dulces están en el punto perfecto. Nosotros pedimos para llevar.

This is my favorite bread for buttered toast.
Can’t wait to try all of their pastries 🍞🥐

The food was good, but the kimchi croquette was a little spicy and when I ask about this they told me no so I waste my money in that lol, but I recommend the garlic croassant and the mango one was delicious
Great bakery and wonderful staff! My favorite place to buy treats!

We went to the southend location just after it opened and found many bakery items over and they were not refilling them that day. They were also out of Fresh baked savory items.

But, we definitely recommend the Piedmont location. The ambience and food in that location is much better than here.

Quaint small bakery with a wide assortment of fresh baked products. Would be nice to see pricing prior to selecting items on a tray and snaking through the store. Special breads like chestnut need chestnuts spread more evenly  throughout the bread
Bakery items are phenomenal. This has to be the best bakery I've ever been to. Would highly recommend others to come
Almond croissants are the best!

This bakery in Charlotte is a croissant and bread lover's paradise! They offer an incredible variety, and the quality is outstanding. The coffee was delightful, and the service was impeccable - friendly and attentive. The ambiance of the bakery creates a cozy and welcoming atmosphere. I’ll be definitely back for more!
The pasteries were AMAZING, I didn't get a special coffee but next time definitely will!! Even though it was so busy the staff was so pleasant and efficient. Overall a great experience!
Super cute spot. The pastries tasted as good as they smelled. The 4-stars is only because of limited seating and parking; it’s definitely a grab-and-go spot but a delish spot to check out!

Every pastry we tried was amazingggg. First time having the honey cheese pancakes Omg so delicious. The doughnuts tasted fresh, the strawberry and crème pastry was *chefs kiss. My boyfriend also had the cookies and cream macaroons and he was annoyed  he only bought one haha! We demolished our pastries even though we wanted to save some for later they were THAT good. I also bought a cheesecake that I can’t wait to have for dessert tonight :) my boyfriend had the strawberry smoothie and said it tasted fresh and not too sweet. The only thing I would say that was slightly disappointing was the butter pecan latte. It was lacking something I just can’t put my finger on it. Overall we will DEFINITELY be back to try other items. Service was amazing as well. Thanks offline for having us!

Everything is so delicious! We love this location, right across from Atherton and we love ALL the sweet and savory treats. The strawberry and mango croissants are my favorite while my husband LOVES the focaccia bread and the croquettes! All the beverages are delicious, the honey lavender matcha latte is *CHEFS KISS* and the service is top notch.
Phenomenal pastries and desserts! Everything seemed super fresh. Bonus points for friendly staff!
I love this place ♥️🫶 super sweet and everything fresh and good quality. I came almost every day for my pink bread and my Icedd butter pecan with oatmilk . Lol love it
The pastries and bread are amazing! Im not sure what I got but it’s not too sweet, which I love, and the dough is SUPER soft. Def should buy from!
I was blown away at how good these macarons are! I will absolutely be back soon to try their variety of breads and pastries

Oh lucky day! They were having a BOGO event today so we had a chance to try something new. We went with our trusty strawberry croissant and tried a new treat, the sweet rice donut. The croissant was chef's kiss as always. The donut was delightful too with a mochi base.
Everything was amazing and fresh! People were super nice and friendly! I will be coming back for sure!!! Thank you i have been waiting for a place like this forever!

Delicious!!!! Their lemonade isn’t too sweet which is how I prefer it ! They have different varieties of pastries which are delicious and fresh ! Definitely will be going often especially for their curry croquettes!!

Finally open after signs have been out for months. Another great addition to South End food portfolio.
Compared to the other two locations in Charlotte, this one is more of a middle size - has some tables but not for large groups. I was told that the patisserie selection would be fairly similar to each other. I went here by noon so most of the patisseries were freshly baked and there were almost the full selection - not sure what it would look like closer to evening.
My favorite - the garlic cream cheese bread - was shaped differently with the flower-cut on the top. It tasted a bit sweeter compared to the one I bought from South Park location… but all good. Cute place to stop by for something light, or bring home for next day breakfast.

raw_data.description:
Freshly Baked, Everyday

Since our launch into the United States in 2004, TOUS les JOURS [meaning "everyday" in French] has developed into a reputable neighborhood bakery specializing in French-Asian inspired baked goods, hand crafted beverages and bold, flavorful coffee and espresso made with the finest ingredients.

With a commitment to using only the finest ingredients, our products are known for their unique flavors and wholesome qualities. Our skilled bakers create a wide array of delicious treats that are freshly baked and ready to be enjoyed by our customers seeking exceptional taste and quality.

reviews_data.review_text: Stopped in here because Snooze was taking too long to seat us,  and O...EM..GEE!!! If you like, no, IF YOU LOVE PASTRIES AND BREADS, you gotta hit this place up! The selection is  very decent for light pastries (croissants, breads, Danish, etc), not to mwntuonthe various flavors of croissants and refrigerated desserts! And the crew is amazing! Stepping in here felt like stepping into a bistro in Europe!

review_questions.Parking options: Free parking lot, Free street parking

reviews_data.review_text: My french friend love it. She said it taste so authentic and she felt like back in her home country!
The cafe vibe is cozy and inviting, perfect for a casual coffee break or a sweet treat on the go.

All our food (custard bun, red bean bun, melon bread, croissant, and macaroons) tastes like febreeze air freshener. I literally have nothing else bad to say. Surely it could have been a one off occurrence, I’ve only been here once. For every single item I listed to have that chemical air freshener taste though…yeah I would never go here again.
among the worst locations

Love this place! Staff is friendly and helpful! Love their cakes and pastries, even the savory ones like curry and kimchi! The sandwich with the cheese on the outside and ham on the inside is so good. Try their honey lavender matcha. My faaaav!
Best cakes in Charlotte can't go wrong go in there
Very good service from the staff and the great taste from the food. Clean area,  grea atmosphere.  I will come back  and bring my family and friends.  Continue this way.

Love this location! It’s a bit smaller than the others but feels more cozy. The staff is always super friendly and help me with coffee recommendations when I don’t know what to order. Never had an issue with ordering and their cakes are always a big hit at family parties.
Love Tous!!! The staff is so friendly and welcoming!!!

I’ve been coming to this bakery for years, and I have to say — the recent changes in management have truly elevated the experience! The atmosphere feels warm and welcoming, and the staff are friendly and attentive. You can really tell they care about providing great service and high-quality products.

The pastries and bread are as delicious as ever (if not better!), and everything tastes so fresh. The new management has introduced some exciting new items while keeping the classic favorites we all love.

It’s clear they are focused on creating a positive environment for both customers and the team. Change can be tough, but in this case, it feels like a step in the right direction.

Highly recommend stopping by if you haven't visited in a while — you’ll definitely notice the difference!

Customer service was terrible. I felt very disrespected despite doing nothing wrong. I felt as if the person working at the cash register had some sort of ingrained hate specifically towards me based on their tone and body language. They didn’t do this to other people who were in the line. I don’t understand why I had to be the unlucky target. Totally ruined my day. 🙁💔👎🏾
Great customer service, and the pastry was amazing!! Love this for first time experience

Adorable bakery. Has a seating area. Staff greets you immediately & they were super friendly. Great customer service & great pastries. They are pretty creative with drinks that have matcha. Definitely coming here more often.

Incredible place! Everything is fantastic! And the service is outstanding!
Claudia Ribas
Amazing pastries and cute little spot.
One of my favorite coffee shops in charlotte!!! The workers here are friendly and the pastries are amazing!

I’m a regular at this place. I’m obsessed with their honey lavender matcha that I get it at least once a week. The donuts are also very delicious.  I am always greeted every time I walk through the door. Everyone is always so sweet. Sometimes I sit at the back of the other place and the staff are always telling me to go sit down and they will bring my drink out to me when they don’t have to. They’re part of the reason I keep coming back.
The atmosphere was amazingly beautiful the food was great and the service was great

Me, my daughter and grandson were so excited to try this place Tous Les Jours Southend on Sunday, June 1, 2025. We went to the South Blvd location. As we entered, we were never greeted with a "hello" or anything. We looked at most of the pastries and desserts that were in the cases, but still no greeting or acknowledgement by the staff that we were even there. We finally asked one of the employees if they usually greet customers as they come in, and the young man replied, "yes" sarcastically. So we ended up leaving. One thing about me, if I'm not greeted or acknowledged after entering an establishment, I will not spend one penny there. We were so disappointed by the way we were ignored. We will not be back either! I wouldn't give them not even one star.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hey Tammy, 

We do apologize about the situation, but upon talking to our employees there seem to be a misunderstanding.  One of our employee did greet your party while he was washing the dishes, and our other employee at the time was helping another customer.  Again we do apologize for the misunderstanding, but the greeting might just be covered by the water.

reviews_data.review_text: They need better staff, the staff there is condescending and got my order wrong. I ordered an ice latte and they gave me a Frappuccino I’m very disappointed and the other time they thought I wasn’t there and spoke bad about me as the customer this is just very disappointing and unprofessional
The best tasting n fresh cakes and macaroons for sure. Used to be a fan for this place in other states and no exceptions here. But the price has definitely gone higher in 5 years.

작지만  깔끔하고 잘 정렬되어있었음.
바게뜨가 한국 뚜레쥬르 바게뜨랑 다르게 생겼음.
소금빵 맛있기를  기대하고있음. 집에 가서 먹어야지  ㅎㅎ
Nice selection of French desserts. Their cloud cake is a unique recipe.
i love this place. always here
Walked in at 7:40 PM and was told they stop serving lattes after 7:30 PM. Seriously? It’s a café, not a bank. If you close at 8, why cut off drinks early? Pretty disappointing.
A French bakery conveniently located in Southend, however the melon bread and blueberry cake lacked richness in their taste. Spend your money elsewhere.
Absolutely stunning bakery. Service is acceptable.

Demasiado rico todo!! Muy buena combinación de repostería francesa y asiática, las bebidas también estuvieron muy buenas, el personal atento, aunque pocas personas y en un momento se llenó y hubo un poco de demora.
Staff is RUDE - food is great tho

Decided to drop by while in Charlotte because not many of TLJ in the area. Options are limited compared to their bigger locations but I found what i was looking for. The pastries, cakes and drinks were good. Taking off one star for the female cashier who was rude and had a sarcastic attitude. The guy who made our drinks was nice though.

Because of the limited space, I’ll give the atmosphere a 4. It’s fine to sit but if all few seats are taken, you’ll need to find another place to relax. The food is light and to perfection. There is a desert for everyone here. The cakes are not dense and I would be careful for those who like dense cakes.

The hours are accessible for everyone and just like every bakery, unfortunately the early birds get the best food.

I haven’t tried their drinks or was inclined to go to their boba shop to order anything.

The baristas always have a positive attitude even with a large amount of people.

Personally I like the simple classics like their croissants and vanilla or cookies and cream macaroons. I have eaten their cloud cakes, other macaroons, soft breads (milk cream is my fav as it’s basic).

It’s a fun place to try different things and share amongst friends and when you find your favorite- go back for more.

So we walked in yesterday afternoon, and I asked for iced coffee, black. The young lady that was attending the counter literally replied: “no, we don’t have that”. I look up at the menu and clearly see iced coffee listed as an option. I then said: “ok… can I have an americano, iced?” as I read off the menu and she then proceeded to make the said iced coffee. Why was she so quick to say no to my request, just because I didn’t ask for what was on the menu? No Customer Service or people skills! Coffee was just ok and mango doughnut had too much crème.

I specifically drove 1.5 hours to try their croissants as it's something my kid and I love to do. Find cute bakery's with our favorites pastry's. When you enter the building the atmosphere is less than enthusiastic. I felt like I was coming in during a closing shift at 2pm. The doughnuts were dry but it was midday when I got it. Cream filled doughnut was great, croissants were buttery and flakey as well as the raspberry danish. Cute place, but the outward appearance  is begging you to spend time in there but the employees give off a get in and get out attitude. Wasn't really pleasant but the bake goods were pretty good overall.

This place is a solid spot for fresh pastries and coffee. Their almond and strawberry croissants are flaky and rich. The mango and strawberry croissants are super light and not too sweet. Everything is freshly made and baked. The staff is friendly, and the place is cozy with a great ambiance. Definitely worth checking out if you’re in the area.

reviews_data.review_text: My favourite backery place. I first tried it in Korea and I am really happy I can enjoy it here too. People is lovely and the food is wonderful as always
Immaculate vibes and super good pastries honestly.  So happy I discovered this place!

This is one of my go to places for a last minute cake.

I am appreciative of the little kit that is given with the purchase of a whole cake (serving utensil, match, & candles)

There is a little bit of everything for everyone.
There are also some savory options if you're not craving something sweet.

Depending on the time of day, getting in/ out of this location may be an issue (I think it just depends on traffic) , other than that, no other concerns.

This was our first time going to this bakery. It was really pretty and the atmosphere was nice and comfortable. It's mostly self serve which takes a lot if pressure off when trying a new place where there's a lot of options. However, the only negative thing was the lady checking us out. She was very rude and didn't have good customer service skills. Didn't even greet us in and spoke to us very aggressively and bluntly when we were checking out. I normally don't make a review like this but since it was our first time there it just felt necessary. Will try a different location next time.
Croissants and Tiramisu are my favorite breakfast options . Love the combo!!!
Muy bien el servicio es excelente y el producto es delicioso lo recomiendo

I searched out this location via Google and was excited about the the purchase of the Chocolate heart cake for my wife on Valentine Day, presentation was beautiful, but the cake was awful and lacked the taste of anything resembling Chocolate, for the price point we were very disappointed, if you're a true chocolate lover proceed with caution!!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hey Billy, we do apologize for the situation, can you please email us at tljsouthend@gmail.com.

reviews_data.review_text: I absolutely love the matcha at Tous les Jours! If you’re a matcha fan, you have to try the matcha cream and strawberry croissant—it’s the perfect combo. The flaky croissant with the creamy matcha and fresh strawberries is heavenly. Highly recommend stopping by for this treat!

Bad service, stale cakes( as well as the cream in one of their banana bread was wrong - it was not whipped cream), uncomfortable chairs (seemed like this cafe is more focused towards female customers)
Everything I had was delicious. I totally get all the hype that I have heard from different people. The workers were all very friendly and very accommodating. I will definitely be coming back.

So happy I discovered this bakery. The pastries are out of this world and the staff is so nice, so friendly.
Nice place for Bekery but small parking lot.
Pre-ordered a Cloud Cake for my mom’s birthday and it came out beautifully. Staff 10/10! Would recommend!!!

Stopped in to satisfy a sweet craving and Tous Les didn't disappoint. The workers were pleasant and the store was very clean. We purchased several types of pastries to get a feel of the quality. Everything was very fresh and delicious. There is very limited seating on the stores front area but more in the back.
Parking is very hard .

Do not buy cakes from this place. I ordered my daughter’s birthday cake from here and the Assistant manager explained the sizes and prices and I orders an 8 inch cake a simple vanilla cloud cake. And I paid $59 and when I realized that they gave me a 6 inch the smallest cake they got. Also when you called to let them know that I’m sending my daughter to pick up the cake they were trying to sell me the happy birthday sign. Which was $4 when the assistant manager already explained that the cake came with a happy birthday sign in chocolate so the Assistant manager or the store manager Tiffany couldn’t be trusted. They should be ashamed for charging so much money for a 6 inch cake. I work in the food industry as a GM and if I was the Manager there If this happened I would resign immediately. This company has three locations and I bet this maybe how they opened two new stores by cheating customers. I would never step into this store and will make sure to let everyone I know about this place-
Also I purchased small mocha called that’s packaged it tasted stale and upon checking the best by date was expired already. Customers it’s better to buy freshly made cakes at publics for less where they constantly check on the expiration dates.
Makes you wonder if the NC health department needs visit these bakeries more frequently.

I love the other location but for some reason this location is hard to keep giving chances. It’s closer to me and no matter how early you go items are never out/stocked properly. A lot of items are packed up now which makes the items very wet and soggy. For some items it would be impossible to put inside a toaster to hit due to its contents for example the mango doughnut. It’s very disappointing trying to give this location a try and being disappointed each time. I will have to be willing to make the drive out for better quality.

I’ve ordered my daughter birthday cakes from here a few times. She absolutely loves Tous Les Jours cakes. Their cakes are always so delicious, they never disappoint. This facility is small and cozy and not much parking. Staff were extremely friendly. I would definitely recommend.
Cute place.

Loved everything about this bakery. The breads and cake were so delicious! I bought so much to try! I even bought two drinks to try. The good thing is the bakery even gave free complimentary water if you didn’t want to purchase a drink. The atmosphere was very calming. Mind you, I did go to the bakery on a weekday around 4:30ish when it wasn’t so busy. I’m sure it’s busy on the weekends.
Ricos y frescos dulces son perfectos. Y hay variedad en sabores.
Just found my new fav dessert spot! I will be back
My favorite bakery in Charlotte , many items but my favorite is their chocolate covered croissants and strawberry cloud cake .
Amazing bakery items!
Such a cute spot! The food is to die for and the staff is really friendly! Prices are also amazing. Only downside is the parking isn’t great😅 thankfully there’s a garage across the street!

reviews_data.review_text: It's always nice to go to Tous Les Jours, nice French-Korean Bakery, good combination. Service is the best.

Delicious fresh baked goods with a cozy atmosphere and welcoming staff.

We tried multiple sweet and savory treats and everything was fresh and yummy.

I wish they had a larger dinning area with more tables as it got crowded really quickly.

Great experience overall. Highly recommend this place.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much!! We have more seating in the back!

reviews_data.review_text: My new favorite go to spots to wfh! Pastries are delicious! Atmosphere was very cute! The person that helped me a lot was Simon he answered all my questions and was really friendly! Definitely will be coming back regularly!

Beautiful Cafe & Great staff! Southend location of Tour Le Jour is smaller, but the ambiance & service is top-notch! Everybody must try, it’s such a great place to work, socialize. Music is always amazing.

reviews_data.review_text: I’m visiting from Savannah Georgia and this place was amazing tasted delicious it was so cute and the two girls in the front were so sweet definitely will come back when we visit again.

Popped in to see if the prices were any better than back East. Sure enough, it was about $2-3 cheaper, so I couldn't resist grabbing one even though we had dinner plans. The staff was super friendly, and that bread was so good, we came back after dinner and picked up two more.

That milk cream bread is no joke - it might just be the best thing Tous les Jours has going. Seriously, it's a winner no matter where you get it!
Great choice of pastries, cakes and drinks. There are couple tables to sit down and couple parking spots. Very tiny space with cozy atmosphere.

I used to love coming here for fresh pastries but now they are wrapping each individual pastry in plastic and they are now soggy and sad instead of crisp and fresh. Why did you all do this? It defies logic to put fresh pastries into plastic…
reviews_data.owner_answer: First of all we would like to thank you for being a loyal customer.  Due to rising temperatures and humidity the flies and gnats are becoming a big problem in our bakery, and wrapping them is the best solution for everyone to still be able to enjoy our bake goods.  We suggest to the pastry in the toaster oven or air fryer for a couple minutes, that way it will be crispy again.  Thank you again for visiting, we do apologize for this inconvenience.

reviews_data.review_text: Strawberry cloud cake and  mango could piece was good
Place is small but the food tastes good. Their cloud cake and kimchi croquette is one of my fav.

Starting to notice all of the Tous Le Jours locations are either cutting back or just removing all of the savory items off their selection of baked goods entirely. This was the only spot left in the surrounding Charlotte area that still carried the hotdog breads, and sadly, they are no longer here. Very disappointing. One of the only reasons I even visit. Not much of a sweets person, so depriving a clientele base that prefer "savory" over "sweets" seems ill-advised. 😒😮‍💨
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hey Louis, sorry for the inconvenience. We will be bring the savory items back soon we just removed for now, we are doing some adjustments.

reviews_data.review_text: I loved this place but recently they have not been making any of the savory foods, of course their sweet treats are great but the main reason I keep coming back is for their savory breakfast/brunch items. Now that they are not serving them I will unfortunately have to find another bakery to visit - until they bring back the croquettes.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Jodi, sorry for the inconvenience we will definitely be bring back all the savory food. We are in the process of getting our croquet warmer fixed.

reviews_data.review_text: The breads and desserts were delicious! Customer service was good, and the atmosphere was pleasant. There are many delicious options to choose from.

I tried this charming French-Asian bakery and was blown away by the innovative fusion of flavors and textures. The pastries, such as the croissants, donuts with passion fruit-manggo filling and varieties of cakes with matcha and fruity flavors, were familiar, exotic  and a delightful twist to traditional French baked goods. The bakery's commitment to using high-quality, locally sourced ingredients shone through in every bite, making it a must-visit destination for anyone looking to indulge in a unique and delicious culinary experience. As a Filipino, the glutinous rice donut reminded me of home and the dessert that my grandma loves to whip when  I was young. Indeed , mus-visit  !!

Walked in at open and had a nasty encounter with employee!!! 1st. ... only 10% of their baked goods were even out with multiple people working??? A young female was super nasty, corrected me with so much attitude and horrible conduct even after I apologized and left a tip (for the other sweet girl). At the end of checking out, I nicely mention to her that there are a few gnats in the bakery case - she never looked up at me and had an irritated face the entire time. I get it ... its morning time and you gotta work but learn to treat and talk to people with love. The other girl in there is always a doll, FYI.
Good pastry options. Great service.

Went here on a whim just looked up close bakeries , and I there were so many good options I  like barely decided I ended up leaving with 5 items came out to 27 dollars and everything was so good !! Literally blown away definitely coming back to try more and get coffee next time!

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Mango Cream Donut, Apple Turnover, Almond Croissant

reviews_data.review_text: Stopped here for the first time after leaving Snooze in the same strip. I'm so happy we did. Lots of fresh bakery items as well as lattes, tea, coffee, and Frappuccinos. We purchased the Caramel Apple Pie danish to take home. There is limited seating. Outdoor parking. Pleasant personnel.  We will be returning.

Absolutely live this place!
-it’s all fresh and made daily
- The cake is SO GOOD! It’s fluffy and is topped with a whipped frosting
- Whatever they don’t sell they typically donate it to local business
- In my opinion cheap prices

Tous les Jours which means “every day” in French is a South Korean bakery franchise. This place is one of the finest bakeries with fantastic ambience. Coming to pastry section, We have ordered Guava Danish, Strawberry Croissant and Chocolate croissant. Guava Danish was the winner. Green tea cloud cake and choco cloud cake were light, mouth watering and goes very well with latte. Raisin bread was fluffy, aromatic and has the right amount I of sweetness. Caramel cheesecake was little bit over sweet. Coming to coffee, Iced tiramisu latte, vanilla latte, lavender latte and cappuccino were outstanding.
Staff are not friendly. The place was dirty and seemed junky. We actually love this franchise and was disappointed by this location. I’d recommend to go to South Park and not waste your time.
Shaniyah and Mozi were amazing explaining the menu and making suggestions. Wonderful customer service we will be back, great experience for our 1st time
The selection is amazing, the treats are all tasty. A good mix of savory and sweet. All the drinks are great, the place is cute. I would come here everyday if I could.
Literally the best cakes in Charlotte, so delicious, the inside of the store is always clean and the staff are amazing! Super accommodating and always make sure I leave happy.
Delicious!

im french and this is my favorite bakery in charlotte so far

chocolate avalanche: 12/10
strawberry bread: 22/10
croque-monsieur: 10/10

and the strawberry lemonade with a touch of carbonation 😩😩😩😩 made my day

excited to try a lot more things next time we visit

parking sucks tho but the pastries are worth it
I was so excited to visit this place as soon as moved here. Absolutely stunning bakery, delicious foods. will more than likely be back.

Update: went here again on a Sunday and some of the pastries honestly tasted a bit old and stale, not daily fresh but from yesterday. Bit disappointing.

Tried this cafe for the first time and it was great! The pastries were fresh and absolutely delicious! Staff was nice and everything was very clean and pristine. Highly recommend!

The place is really small. There weren't a lot of people inside but it was still a little hard to get around. I like to take my time looking at things, even more so since this was my first time here, but each time I would stop and look it felt like I was holding the people behind me up. Despite this, they offer a TON of baked goods. The staff were incredibly friendly as well. I got a honey castella, honeydew melon bread, taro loaf, honey mochi pancakes, and an iced red velvet latte. They were okay, a little stale but this may have been due to the fact that I ate them at home and not in the store. The red velvet latte was okay too, it didn't really taste like red velvet until I reached the pieces at the bottom of the cup. Overall, not bad but I just wish it was bigger and the seating wasn't so cramped. If I come here again, it will be for the honeydew melon bread 😋
Absolutely wonderful!!!
Fresh baked pastries, bread, and desserts that are OMG amazing!!! They have the best service and even the customers can sell you on what’s good. A hidden treasure in the Queen City.

Heamy fellow Charlatans or soon to be visitors. When in the Queen City, Southend  is where you wanna be if you love French pastries. Tous less Jours is a very warm, posh, and great spot to have great coffee & pastries all day. Just make sure when you go their you experience Brittany's great customer service and lovely smile, Mike's welcoming presence and of course Mozi's craving coffee creations. She's great on detail and meticulous on how she crafts your drink. Also Worker is normally somewhere helping the entire show run smoothly. Thanks guys for the great experience, I shall continue to be a patronizing customer 👌🏿

Finally, I made my way to visit this location for the Yelp experience. First off, this is located right off South Blvd, and let me say parking is rough! There are only a few spaces in front of the shop, and you also have to deal with that rough south end traffic. I went during my lunch break, which I took early just to beat lunchtime traffic. There was no traffic and about 2 parking spaces to choose from. The shop itself is super cute and small. Upon entering, you are greeted with a variety of pastry and bread selections. The ladies at the counter were super nice and helpful. You get a tray in the beginning and your pair of tongs and start selecting any pieces you would like. I got the spinach and feta Danish, which I read tastes better warming up in the oven, which I'm so excited. I ended up wanting to purchase chocolate filled fluffy donut, which I'm so excited to try out! I also bought a vanilla latte, which was def. Needed for this cold weather. It was not too expensive as I thought it would be, and they were actually reasonably prices $3+. I did find out they have other locations, which I def do. Intend on visiting.

Everything here was so good. I love trying new bakeries and this one did not disappoint. For a first-timer, the setup was a little confusing,  it I did like the self-serve aspect since they do get pretty  busy.

Easy to find with one of the most awkward parking lots I’ve seen, Tous Les Jours is an amazing bakery. You walk in the door and the smells immediately make your stomach growl in anticipation.

The two young ladies working there were lovely and polite. They became quite busy soon after I arrived but remained calm, cool and collected.

I had a caramel frappe and a spinach feta pastry while there. Both were very yummy. One of the young ladies packed my to-go bag professionally so nothing was squished by the time I got home.

Everything was so fresh, delicious, and affordable. Can’t wait to go back.

Phenomenal!!! We travel all over for my husbands job. I believe I came across this place from a blog on Pinterest and had it saved on Google maps as a place I wanted to go. We were in town and went here last minute. I don’t have a single sweet tooth but my husband and son do. I can’t even tell you what all they got but I got a piece of strawberry cake, a pumpkin something or other and one thing that looked like a sugar doughnut but was filled with cheese. We bought about $50 of random things because we don’t normally stop by places like this. Even after a few days in the fridge everything was SO good. Nothing was too sweet and the staff was beyond helpful and nice. I’d love to stop by again if we have time before we leave town. If your thinking about trying this place, just do it! I can’t say enough good things about it! Good job y’all!!
Excellent service, the desserts are delicious as is the coffee. I am a coffee lover
Everything looked and tasted amazing! Had a hard time choosing. Everything was so fresh. The staff was so friendly! Vanilla latte was delicious!
Everything I’ve tried here has been excellent and tastes extremely fresh (macarons, croquettes, croissants) and staff has been polite every time I’ve come in! Can’t wait to try more.

I heard their name from my friends in Boston so tried the one in Charlotte. Coffee and cakes were excellent. I wish the place was bigger. It is not a place for having your coffee and working from there.
Amazing deserts, park at chipotle in the morning

This was our second time visiting this bakery and first visit to this particular location. The selection was great, everything looked fresh & delicious, staff was friendly and informative, and we enjoyed everything we purchased. Mango cream donut is one of my favs!

This one is my favorite... always the freshest. All their employees seem so nice, the fact they put certain foods in a heater where the other locations doesn't and it's always full of product ... needless to say I'm in one or the other multiple times a week... they take a whole lot of my money but worth it

Cute cozy spot for coffee and exceptional pastries. Limited seating. All of the sweet pastries deserve a try. I ate as much as I could for the two days I was in town. Quality coffee and attentive staff.
The best food & service,good place
Great atmosphere.  Wonderful customer service.  Amazing pastries.
I like how you can pick your own items.  Very good!

I didn't appreciate the service I received from the manager. She was helping out at the cash register. She stopped being friendly when I looked for a coupon I saw on ig.

The pastries are good! They don't quite compare to how they taste in Korea, but they take care of the itch that I have for French-Korean baked goods

Las muchachas fueron muy amables con nosotros , supimos de este lugar y decidimos ir porque no se encuentra lugares así aquí con panes y dulces que se vean y sepan deliciosos. Lo recomiendo no son costosos tampoco tan dulces están en el punto perfecto. Nosotros pedimos para llevar.

This is my favorite bread for buttered toast.
Can’t wait to try all of their pastries 🍞🥐

The food was good, but the kimchi croquette was a little spicy and when I ask about this they told me no so I waste my money in that lol, but I recommend the garlic croassant and the mango one was delicious
Great bakery and wonderful staff! My favorite place to buy treats!

We went to the southend location just after it opened and found many bakery items over and they were not refilling them that day. They were also out of Fresh baked savory items.

But, we definitely recommend the Piedmont location. The ambience and food in that location is much better than here.

Quaint small bakery with a wide assortment of fresh baked products. Would be nice to see pricing prior to selecting items on a tray and snaking through the store. Special breads like chestnut need chestnuts spread more evenly  throughout the bread
Bakery items are phenomenal. This has to be the best bakery I've ever been to. Would highly recommend others to come
Almond croissants are the best!

This bakery in Charlotte is a croissant and bread lover's paradise! They offer an incredible variety, and the quality is outstanding. The coffee was delightful, and the service was impeccable - friendly and attentive. The ambiance of the bakery creates a cozy and welcoming atmosphere. I’ll be definitely back for more!
The pasteries were AMAZING, I didn't get a special coffee but next time definitely will!! Even though it was so busy the staff was so pleasant and efficient. Overall a great experience!
Super cute spot. The pastries tasted as good as they smelled. The 4-stars is only because of limited seating and parking; it’s definitely a grab-and-go spot but a delish spot to check out!

Every pastry we tried was amazingggg. First time having the honey cheese pancakes Omg so delicious. The doughnuts tasted fresh, the strawberry and crème pastry was *chefs kiss. My boyfriend also had the cookies and cream macaroons and he was annoyed  he only bought one haha! We demolished our pastries even though we wanted to save some for later they were THAT good. I also bought a cheesecake that I can’t wait to have for dessert tonight :) my boyfriend had the strawberry smoothie and said it tasted fresh and not too sweet. The only thing I would say that was slightly disappointing was the butter pecan latte. It was lacking something I just can’t put my finger on it. Overall we will DEFINITELY be back to try other items. Service was amazing as well. Thanks offline for having us!

Everything is so delicious! We love this location, right across from Atherton and we love ALL the sweet and savory treats. The strawberry and mango croissants are my favorite while my husband LOVES the focaccia bread and the croquettes! All the beverages are delicious, the honey lavender matcha latte is *CHEFS KISS* and the service is top notch.
Phenomenal pastries and desserts! Everything seemed super fresh. Bonus points for friendly staff!
I love this place ♥️🫶 super sweet and everything fresh and good quality. I came almost every day for my pink bread and my Icedd butter pecan with oatmilk . Lol love it
The pastries and bread are amazing! Im not sure what I got but it’s not too sweet, which I love, and the dough is SUPER soft. Def should buy from!
I was blown away at how good these macarons are! I will absolutely be back soon to try their variety of breads and pastries

Oh lucky day! They were having a BOGO event today so we had a chance to try something new. We went with our trusty strawberry croissant and tried a new treat, the sweet rice donut. The croissant was chef's kiss as always. The donut was delightful too with a mochi base.
Everything was amazing and fresh! People were super nice and friendly! I will be coming back for sure!!! Thank you i have been waiting for a place like this forever!

Delicious!!!! Their lemonade isn’t too sweet which is how I prefer it ! They have different varieties of pastries which are delicious and fresh ! Definitely will be going often especially for their curry croquettes!!

Finally open after signs have been out for months. Another great addition to South End food portfolio.
Compared to the other two locations in Charlotte, this one is more of a middle size - has some tables but not for large groups. I was told that the patisserie selection would be fairly similar to each other. I went here by noon so most of the patisseries were freshly baked and there were almost the full selection - not sure what it would look like closer to evening.
My favorite - the garlic cream cheese bread - was shaped differently with the flower-cut on the top. It tasted a bit sweeter compared to the one I bought from South Park location… but all good. Cute place to stop by for something light, or bring home for next day breakfast.
